<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 12 at 9:09AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Heavy Snow Through This Morning...
A band of heavy snow will continue moving slowly eastward across
the Mohawk Valley and southern Adirondacks through this morning.
Snowfall rates of 1 to 2 inches per hour will lead to snow
covered roads and poor visibility. This includes the New York
State Thruway in southern Herkimer and Montgomery counties. Avoid
unnecessary travel if possible, as conditions will be hazardous.</description>
